item.description:
One of my favourite features of IntelliJ is that it tracks the item that you currently have open on your Solution Explorer.
I thought this wasn&rsquo;t possible in Visual Studio and had resigned myself to trying to remember which project each file was in. Luckily for me a colleague pointed out that it is in fact possible but is just turned off by default.
Tools &gt; Options &gt; Projects and Solutions &gt; Check &lsquo;Track Active Item in Solution Explorer&rsquo;
